        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName>16 Addison Road | Kensington W</placeName>
                    <date>Nov 22/72</date>
                    <salute>My dear Sir</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>You must have thought me very remiss for not writing to thank you for your kindness in sending me your book, but I have only just returned home after a nearly six months absence &amp; from some mistake the book was never forwarded to me.<ref target="#foot.f1"/></p>
<p>Please accept my best thanks for it now &amp; believe me Dear Sir | Yours very truly | Briton Riviere <lb resp="#mjhawkins"/></p>
<p rend="left">Charles Darwin Esq</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

            
            
        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">Riviere’s name appears on CD’s presentation list for <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_2400.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Expression</hi></ref> (Appendix V); Riviere had made two of the illustrations (see <ref target="../bibliographies/bibl_1581.xml" resp="#mjhawkins"><hi rend="italic">Correspondence</hi></ref> vol. 19, and this volume).</note>
        </div>        
            
